This place has decent pizza. It's definitely not great nor is it lousy. It's one of the better take out pizzas in Harlem among a sea of mostly lousy pizza places throughout the neighborhood. We had a pepperoni pizza which had fresh and decent ingredients. The sauce is a bit too tinny and sweet tasting. Definitely not high quality homemade sauce. The crust was New York style thin. It was okay but could've used more flavor and better texture. Service was quick and friendly. There just isn't anything memorable about the pizza here. Though it's good if you're in in the area and craving pizza.

Pizza Stop!!! great name for this review I like food and I usually don't write reviews for anything. My experience went like this 3/different orders 3 different dates and from there this conclusion comes. One star for delivery quick and the delivery guys are super nice even if you live on the 5th floor of a walk up. The second star is for having your information always at hand and never having to repeat the address more than once but everything else is a mess. 1rst order. Asked for lite on the sauce I guess they didn't understand that lite sauce means very little sauce. 2nd order I asked for green peppers on a Philly cheese steak and they put red peppers and also they put sauce. Who in their right mind puts tomato sauce on a Philly. And 3rd order I wanted a meatlovers pie also the lite sauce that never happened and the next day I got food poisoning. So I wouldn't recommend this place. Sucks because the dough it's pretty good.

So i called the shop back and obviously there's a miscommunication between the young lady who took my order and the guy that called me lying telling me i order for pick up. Maybe they don't delivery to my address and she just wasn't informed But communication is key and they failed terribly in that end.
